From: Krishna Kurapati <krishna.kurapati@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 11 Mar 2025 13:26:58 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] UPSTREAM: arm64: dts: qcom: Add support for usb nodes on
 QCS8300

Add support for USB controllers on QCS8300. The second
controller is only High Speed capable.

Signed-off-by: Krishna Kurapati <krishna.kurapati@oss.qualcomm.com>
Upstream-Status: submitted [https://lore.kernel.org/all/20241114055152.1562116-2-quic_kriskura@quicinc.com/]
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs8300.dtsi | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs8300.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs8300.dtsi
index 998bc69ce4a1..b695c60f649b 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs8300.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs8300.dtsi
@@ -7076,8 +7076,11 @@ usb_1_dwc3: usb@a600000 {
 				iommus = <&apps_smmu 0x80 0x0>;
 				phys = <&usb_1_hsphy>, <&usb_qmpphy>;
 				phy-names = "usb2-phy", "usb3-phy";
-				snps,dis_u2_susphy_quirk;
 				snps,dis_enblslpm_quirk;
+				snps,dis-u1-entry-quirk;
+				snps,dis-u2-entry-quirk;
+				snps,dis_u2_susphy_quirk;
+				snps,dis_u3_susphy_quirk;
 			};
 		};
 
